{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"\"People do stupid things."},{"time":3000,"text":"That's what spreads HIV.\""},{"time":5000,"text":"This was a headline in a U.K. newspaper,"},{"time":7000,"text":"The Guardian, not that long ago."},{"time":9000,"text":"I'm curious, show of hands, who agrees with it?"},{"time":14000,"text":"Well, one or two brave souls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"This is actually a direct quote from an epidemiologist"},{"time":19000,"text":"who's been in field of HIV for 15 years,"},{"time":21000,"text":"worked on four continents,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and you're looking at her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"And I am now going to argue"},{"time":27000,"text":"that this is only half true."},{"time":29000,"text":"People do get HIV because they do stupid things,"},{"time":32000,"text":"but most of them are doing stupid things"},{"time":34000,"text":"for perfectly rational reasons."},{"time":37000,"text":"Now, \"rational\" is the dominant paradigm"},{"time":40000,"text":"in public health,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and if you put your public health nerd glasses on,"},{"time":45000,"text":"you'll see that if we give people the information that they need"},{"time":48000,"text":"about what's good for them and what's bad for them,"},{"time":50000,"text":"if you give them the services"},{"time":52000,"text":"that they can use to act on that information,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and a little bit of motivation,"},{"time":56000,"text":"people will make rational decisions"},{"time":58000,"text":"and live long and healthy lives."},{"time":60000,"text":"Wonderful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"That's slightly problematic for me because I work in HIV,"},{"time":65000,"text":"and although I'm sure you all know"},{"time":67000,"text":"that HIV is about poverty and gender inequality,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and if you were at TED '07"},{"time":72000,"text":"it's about coffee prices ..."},{"time":74000,"text":"Actually, HIV's about sex and drugs,"},{"time":77000,"text":"and if there are two things that make"},{"time":79000,"text":"human beings a little bit irrational,"},{"time":81000,"text":"they are erections and addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"So, let's start with what's rational for an addict."},{"time":89000,"text":"Now, I remember speaking to an Indonesian friend of mine, Frankie."},{"time":92000,"text":"We were having lunch and he was telling me"},{"time":94000,"text":"about when he was in jail in Bali for a drug injection."},{"time":97000,"text":"It was someone's birthday, and they had very kindly"},{"time":99000,"text":"smuggled some heroin into jail,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and he was very generously sharing it out"},{"time":104000,"text":"with all of his colleagues."},{"time":106000,"text":"And so everyone lined up,"},{"time":108000,"text":"all the smackheads in a row,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and the guy whose birthday it was"},{"time":112000,"text":"filled up the fit,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and he went down and started injecting people."},{"time":117000,"text":"So he injects the first guy,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and then he's wiping the needle on his shirt,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and he injects the next guy."},{"time":124000,"text":"And Frankie says, \"I'm number 22 in line,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and I can see the needle coming down towards me,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and there is blood all over the place."},{"time":133000,"text":"It's getting blunter and blunter."},{"time":135000,"text":"And a small part of my brain is thinking,"},{"time":138000,"text":"'That is so gross"},{"time":140000,"text":"and really dangerous,'"},{"time":142000,"text":"but most of my brain is thinking,"},{"time":144000,"text":"'Please let there be some smack left"},{"time":146000,"text":"by the time it gets to me."},{"time":148000,"text":"Please let there be some left.'\""},{"time":150000,"text":"And then, telling me this story,"},{"time":152000,"text":"Frankie said,"},{"time":154000,"text":"\"You know ... God,"},{"time":156000,"text":"drugs really make you stupid.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"And, you know, you can't fault him for accuracy."},{"time":163000,"text":"But, actually, Frankie, at that time,"},{"time":166000,"text":"was a heroin addict and he was in jail."},{"time":168000,"text":"So his choice was either"},{"time":170000,"text":"to accept that dirty needle or not to get high."},{"time":173000,"text":"And if there's one place you really want to get high,"},{"time":175000,"text":"it's when you're in jail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"But I'm a scientist"},{"time":179000,"text":"and I don't like to make data out of anecdotes,"},{"time":181000,"text":"so let's look at some data."},{"time":183000,"text":"We talked to 600 drug addicts"},{"time":186000,"text":"in three cities in Indonesia,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and we said, \"Well, do you know how you get HIV?\""},{"time":190000,"text":"\"Oh yeah, by sharing needles.\""},{"time":192000,"text":"I mean, nearly 100 percent. Yeah, by sharing needles."},{"time":195000,"text":"And, \"Do you know where you can get a clean needle"},{"time":197000,"text":"at a price you can afford to avoid that?\""},{"time":199000,"text":"\"Oh yeah.\" Hundred percent."},{"time":201000,"text":"\"We're smackheads; we know where to get clean needles.\""},{"time":203000,"text":"\"So are you carrying a needle?\""},{"time":205000,"text":"We're actually interviewing people on the street,"},{"time":207000,"text":"in the places where they're hanging out and taking drugs."},{"time":209000,"text":"\"Are you carrying clean needles?\""},{"time":211000,"text":"One in four, maximum."},{"time":214000,"text":"So no surprises then that"},{"time":216000,"text":"the proportion that actually used clean needles"},{"time":218000,"text":"every time they injected in the last week"},{"time":220000,"text":"is just about one in 10,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and the other nine in 10 are sharing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"So you've got this massive mismatch;"},{"time":228000,"text":"everyone knows that"},{"time":230000,"text":"if they share they're going to get HIV,"},{"time":232000,"text":"but they're all sharing anyway."},{"time":234000,"text":"So what's that about? Is it like you get a better high if you share or something?"},{"time":237000,"text":"We asked that to a junkie and they're like, \"Are you nuts?\""},{"time":240000,"text":"You don't want to share a needle anymore than you want"},{"time":242000,"text":"to share a toothbrush even with someone you're sleeping with."},{"time":245000,"text":"There's just kind of an ick factor there."},{"time":247000,"text":"\"No, no. We share needles because we don't want to go to jail.\""},{"time":251000,"text":"So, in Indonesia at this time,"},{"time":254000,"text":"if you were carrying a needle and the cops rounded you up,"},{"time":257000,"text":"they could put you into jail."},{"time":259000,"text":"And that changes the equation slightly, doesn't it?"},{"time":261000,"text":"Because your choice now is either"},{"time":264000,"text":"I use my own needle now,"},{"time":268000,"text":"or I could share a needle now"},{"time":270000,"text":"and get a disease that's going to"},{"time":272000,"text":"possibly kill me 10 years from now,"},{"time":274000,"text":"or I could use my own needle now"},{"time":277000,"text":"and go to jail tomorrow."},{"time":280000,"text":"And while junkies think that"},{"time":282000,"text":"it's a really bad idea to expose themselves to HIV,"},{"time":285000,"text":"they think it's a much worse idea"},{"time":287000,"text":"to spend the next year in jail"},{"time":289000,"text":"where they'll probably end up in Frankie's situation"},{"time":291000,"text":"and expose themselves to HIV anyway."},{"time":294000,"text":"So, suddenly it becomes perfectly rational"},{"time":296000,"text":"to share needles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"Now, let's look at it from a policy maker's point of view."},{"time":300000,"text":"This is a really easy problem."},{"time":302000,"text":"For once, your incentives are aligned."},{"time":305000,"text":"We've got what's rational for public health."},{"time":308000,"text":"You want people to use clean needles --"},{"time":310000,"text":"and junkies want to use clean needles."},{"time":312000,"text":"So we could make this problem go away"},{"time":314000,"text":"simply by making clean needles universally available"},{"time":317000,"text":"and taking away the fear of arrest."},{"time":319000,"text":"Now, the first person to figure that out"},{"time":321000,"text":"and do something about it on a national scale"},{"time":323000,"text":"was that well-known, bleeding heart liberal"},{"time":326000,"text":"Margaret Thatcher."},{"time":328000,"text":"And she put in the world's first"},{"time":330000,"text":"national needle exchange program,"},{"time":332000,"text":"and other countries followed suit: Australia, The Netherlands and few others."},{"time":335000,"text":"And in all of those countries, you can see,"},{"time":337000,"text":"not more than four percent of injectors"},{"time":339000,"text":"ever became infected with HIV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342000,"text":"Now, places that didn't do this -- New York City for example,"},{"time":345000,"text":"Moscow, Jakarta --"},{"time":347000,"text":"we're talking, at its peak,"},{"time":349000,"text":"one in two injectors"},{"time":352000,"text":"infected with this fatal disease."},{"time":355000,"text":"Now, Margaret Thatcher didn't do this"},{"time":357000,"text":"because she has any great love for junkies."},{"time":360000,"text":"She did it because she ran a country"},{"time":363000,"text":"that had a national health service."},{"time":365000,"text":"So, if she didn't invest in effective prevention,"},{"time":368000,"text":"she was going to have pick up the costs"},{"time":370000,"text":"of treatment later on,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and obviously those are much higher."},{"time":374000,"text":"So she was making a politically rational decision."},{"time":377000,"text":"Now, if I take out my"},{"time":379000,"text":"public health nerd glasses here"},{"time":381000,"text":"and look at these data,"},{"time":384000,"text":"it seems like a no-brainer, doesn't it?"},{"time":387000,"text":"But in this country,"},{"time":389000,"text":"where the government apparently does not feel compelled"},{"time":392000,"text":"to provide health care for citizens, (Laughter)"},{"time":394000,"text":"we've taken a very different approach."},{"time":397000,"text":"So what we've been doing in the United States"},{"time":399000,"text":"is reviewing the data -- endlessly reviewing the data."},{"time":402000,"text":"So, these are reviews of hundreds of studies"},{"time":405000,"text":"by all the big muckety-mucks"},{"time":407000,"text":"of the scientific pantheon in the United States,"},{"time":410000,"text":"and these are the studies that show"},{"time":412000,"text":"needle programs are effective -- quite a lot of them."},{"time":414000,"text":"Now, the ones that show that needle programs aren't effective --"},{"time":417000,"text":"you think that's one of these annoying dynamic slides"},{"time":420000,"text":"and I'm going to press my dongle and the rest of it's going to come up,"},{"time":422000,"text":"but no -- that's the whole slide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427000,"text":"There is nothing on the other side."},{"time":432000,"text":"So, completely irrational,"},{"time":434000,"text":"you would think."},{"time":436000,"text":"Except that, wait a minute, politicians are rational, too,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and they're responding to what they think the voters want."},{"time":442000,"text":"So what we see is that voters respond"},{"time":444000,"text":"very well to things like this"},{"time":446000,"text":"and not quite so well to things like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"So it becomes quite rational"},{"time":459000,"text":"to deny services to injectors."},{"time":462000,"text":"Now let's talk about sex."},{"time":464000,"text":"Are we any more rational about sex?"},{"time":467000,"text":"Well, I'm not even going to address"},{"time":469000,"text":"the clearly irrational positions"},{"time":471000,"text":"of people like the Catholic Church,"},{"time":473000,"text":"who think somehow that if you give out condoms,"},{"time":476000,"text":"everyone's going to run out and have sex."},{"time":480000,"text":"I don't know if Pope Benedict"},{"time":482000,"text":"watches TEDTalks online,"},{"time":484000,"text":"but if you do, I've got news for you Benedict --"},{"time":487000,"text":"I carry condoms all the time"},{"time":490000,"text":"and I never get laid."},{"time":492000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":494000,"text":"It's not that easy!"},{"time":496000,"text":"Here, maybe you'll have better luck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504000,"text":"Okay, seriously,"},{"time":506000,"text":"HIV is actually not that easy"},{"time":509000,"text":"to transmit sexually."},{"time":511000,"text":"So, it depends on how much virus there is"},{"time":513000,"text":"in your blood and in your body fluids."},{"time":515000,"text":"And what we've got is a very, very high level of virus"},{"time":518000,"text":"right at the beginning when you're first infected,"},{"time":520000,"text":"then you start making antibodies,"},{"time":522000,"text":"and then it bumps along at quite low levels"},{"time":524000,"text":"for a long time -- 10 or 12 years --"},{"time":526000,"text":"you have spikes if you get another sexually transmitted infection."},{"time":529000,"text":"But basically, nothing much is going on"},{"time":531000,"text":"until you start to get symptomatic AIDS,"},{"time":533000,"text":"and by that stage,"},{"time":535000,"text":"you're not looking great, you're not feeling great,"},{"time":537000,"text":"you're not having that much sex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"So the sexual transmission of HIV"},{"time":541000,"text":"is essentially determined by how many partners you have"},{"time":544000,"text":"in these very short spaces of time"},{"time":547000,"text":"when you have peak viremia."},{"time":549000,"text":"Now, this makes people crazy"},{"time":552000,"text":"because it means that you have to talk about"},{"time":555000,"text":"some groups having more sexual partners"},{"time":557000,"text":"in shorter spaces of time than other groups,"},{"time":559000,"text":"and that's considered stigmatizing."},{"time":561000,"text":"I've always been a bit curious about that"},{"time":563000,"text":"because I think stigma is a bad thing,"},{"time":565000,"text":"whereas lots of sex is quite a good thing,"},{"time":567000,"text":"but we'll leave that be."},{"time":570000,"text":"The truth is that 20 years"},{"time":572000,"text":"of very good research"},{"time":574000,"text":"have shown us that"},{"time":576000,"text":"there are groups that are more likely to turnover"},{"time":579000,"text":"large numbers of partners in a short space of time."},{"time":581000,"text":"And those groups are, globally,"},{"time":583000,"text":"people who sell sex and their more regular partners."},{"time":586000,"text":"They are gay men on the party scene"},{"time":588000,"text":"who have, on average, three times more partners"},{"time":590000,"text":"than straight people on the party scene."},{"time":592000,"text":"And they are heterosexuals"},{"time":594000,"text":"who come from countries that have"},{"time":596000,"text":"traditions of polygamy"},{"time":598000,"text":"and relatively high levels of female autonomy,"},{"time":601000,"text":"and almost all of those countries are in east or southern Africa."},{"time":604000,"text":"And that is reflected in the epidemic that we have today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607000,"text":"You can see these horrifying figures from Africa."},{"time":610000,"text":"These are all countries in southern Africa"},{"time":612000,"text":"where between one in seven,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and one in three"},{"time":616000,"text":"of all adults,"},{"time":618000,"text":"are infected with HIV."},{"time":620000,"text":"Now, in the rest of the world,"},{"time":622000,"text":"we've got basically nothing going on in the general population --"},{"time":625000,"text":"very, very low levels --"},{"time":627000,"text":"but we have extraordinarily high levels of HIV"},{"time":630000,"text":"in these other populations who are at highest risk:"},{"time":633000,"text":"drug injectors, sex workers"},{"time":635000,"text":"and gay men."},{"time":637000,"text":"And you'll note, that's the local data from Los Angeles:"},{"time":639000,"text":"25 percent prevalence among gay men."},{"time":643000,"text":"Of course, you can't get HIV just by having unprotected sex."},{"time":646000,"text":"You can only HIV by having unprotected sex"},{"time":649000,"text":"with a positive person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652000,"text":"In most of the world,"},{"time":654000,"text":"these few prevention failures"},{"time":656000,"text":"notwithstanding,"},{"time":658000,"text":"we are actually doing quite well these days"},{"time":660000,"text":"in commercial sex:"},{"time":662000,"text":"condom use rates are between 80 and 100 percent"},{"time":664000,"text":"in commercial sex in most countries."},{"time":667000,"text":"And, again, it's because of an alignment of the incentives."},{"time":670000,"text":"What's rational for public health"},{"time":672000,"text":"is also rational for individual sex workers"},{"time":674000,"text":"because it's really bad for business to have another STI."},{"time":677000,"text":"No one wants it."},{"time":679000,"text":"And, actually, clients don't want to go home with a drip either."},{"time":681000,"text":"So essentially, you're able to achieve"},{"time":684000,"text":"quite high rates of condom use in commercial sex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"But in \"intimate\" relations"},{"time":689000,"text":"it's much more difficult because,"},{"time":691000,"text":"with your wife or your boyfriend"},{"time":693000,"text":"or someone that you hope might turn into one of those things,"},{"time":696000,"text":"we have this illusion of romance"},{"time":699000,"text":"and trust and intimacy,"},{"time":701000,"text":"and nothing is quite so unromantic"},{"time":704000,"text":"as the, \"My condom or yours, darling?\" question."},{"time":707000,"text":"So in the face of that,"},{"time":710000,"text":"you really need quite a strong incentive"},{"time":713000,"text":"to use condoms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716000,"text":"This, for example, this gentleman is called Joseph."},{"time":719000,"text":"He's from Haiti and he has AIDS."},{"time":721000,"text":"And he's probably not having a lot of sex right now,"},{"time":724000,"text":"but he is a reminder in the population,"},{"time":726000,"text":"of why you might want to be"},{"time":728000,"text":"using condoms."},{"time":730000,"text":"This is also in Haiti and is a reminder"},{"time":732000,"text":"of why you might want to be having sex, perhaps."},{"time":736000,"text":"Now, funnily enough, this is also Joseph"},{"time":739000,"text":"after six months on antiretroviral treatment."},{"time":743000,"text":"Not for nothing do we call it the Lazarus Effect."},{"time":748000,"text":"But it is changing the equation"},{"time":751000,"text":"of what's rational"},{"time":753000,"text":"in sexual decision-making."},{"time":756000,"text":"So, what we've got --"},{"time":758000,"text":"some people say, \"Oh, it doesn't matter very much"},{"time":760000,"text":"because, actually, treatment is effective prevention"},{"time":763000,"text":"because it lowers your viral load and therefore"},{"time":765000,"text":"makes it more difficult to transmit HIV.\""},{"time":767000,"text":"So, if you look at the viremia thing again,"},{"time":770000,"text":"if you do start treatment when you're sick,"},{"time":772000,"text":"well, what happens? Your viral load comes down."},{"time":775000,"text":"But compared to what? What happens if you're not on treatment?"},{"time":779000,"text":"Well, you die,"},{"time":781000,"text":"so your viral load goes to zero."},{"time":783000,"text":"And all of this green stuff here, including the spikes --"},{"time":786000,"text":"which are because you couldn't get to the pharmacy,"},{"time":790000,"text":"or you ran out of drugs, or you went on a three day party binge"},{"time":793000,"text":"and forgot to take your drugs,"},{"time":795000,"text":"or because you've started to get resistance, or whatever --"},{"time":798000,"text":"all of that is virus"},{"time":800000,"text":"that wouldn't be out there, except for treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"Now, am I saying, \"Oh, well, great prevention strategy."},{"time":806000,"text":"Let's just stop treating people.\""},{"time":808000,"text":"Of course not, of course not."},{"time":810000,"text":"We need to expand antiretroviral treatment as much as we can."},{"time":813000,"text":"But what I am doing is calling into question"},{"time":815000,"text":"those people who say that more treatment"},{"time":817000,"text":"is all the prevention we need."},{"time":819000,"text":"That's simply not necessarily true,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and I think we can learn a lot from the experience of gay men"},{"time":824000,"text":"in rich countries where treatment has been widely available"},{"time":827000,"text":"for going on 15 years now."},{"time":829000,"text":"And what we've seen is"},{"time":831000,"text":"that, actually, condom use rates,"},{"time":833000,"text":"which were very, very high --"},{"time":835000,"text":"the gay community responded very rapidly to HIV,"},{"time":838000,"text":"with extremely little help"},{"time":840000,"text":"from public health nerds, I would say --"},{"time":842000,"text":"that condom use rate has come down dramatically since treatment"},{"time":845000,"text":"for two reasons really:"},{"time":847000,"text":"One is the assumption of, \"Oh well,"},{"time":849000,"text":"if he's infected, he's probably on meds,"},{"time":851000,"text":"and his viral load's going to be low, so I'm pretty safe.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"And the other thing is that people are simply"},{"time":856000,"text":"not as scared of HIV"},{"time":858000,"text":"as they were of AIDS, and rightly so."},{"time":861000,"text":"AIDS was a disfiguring disease that killed you,"},{"time":864000,"text":"and HIV is an invisible virus"},{"time":866000,"text":"that makes you take a pill every day."},{"time":868000,"text":"And that's boring,"},{"time":870000,"text":"but is it as boring as"},{"time":873000,"text":"having to use a condom every time you have sex,"},{"time":875000,"text":"no matter how drunk you are,"},{"time":877000,"text":"no matter how many poppers you've taken, whatever?"},{"time":880000,"text":"If we look at the data, we can see that"},{"time":882000,"text":"the answer to that question"},{"time":884000,"text":"is, mmm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886000,"text":"So these are data from Scotland."},{"time":888000,"text":"You see the peak in drug injectors"},{"time":890000,"text":"before they started the national needle exchange program."},{"time":892000,"text":"Then it came way down."},{"time":894000,"text":"And both in heterosexuals -- mostly in commercial sex --"},{"time":896000,"text":"and in drug users,"},{"time":898000,"text":"you've really got nothing much going on after treatment begins,"},{"time":901000,"text":"and that's because of that alignment of incentives"},{"time":903000,"text":"that I talked about earlier."},{"time":905000,"text":"But in gay men,"},{"time":907000,"text":"you've got quite a dramatic rise"},{"time":909000,"text":"starting three or four years"},{"time":911000,"text":"after treatment became widely available."},{"time":913000,"text":"This is of new infections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":917000,"text":"It means that the combined effect of being less worried"},{"time":920000,"text":"and having more virus out there in the population --"},{"time":923000,"text":"more people living longer, healthier lives,"},{"time":925000,"text":"more likely to be getting laid"},{"time":927000,"text":"with HIV --"},{"time":929000,"text":"is outweighing the effects of lower viral load,"},{"time":932000,"text":"and that's a very worrisome thing."},{"time":934000,"text":"What does it mean?"},{"time":936000,"text":"It means we need to be doing more prevention the more treatment we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939000,"text":"Is that what's happening?"},{"time":941000,"text":"No, and I call it the \"compassion conundrum.\""},{"time":944000,"text":"We've talked a lot about compassion the last couple of days,"},{"time":947000,"text":"and what's happening really is that people are"},{"time":950000,"text":"unable quite to bring themselves to put in"},{"time":952000,"text":"good sexual and reproductive health services for sex workers,"},{"time":955000,"text":"unable quite to be giving out needles to junkies."},{"time":958000,"text":"But once they've gone from being"},{"time":961000,"text":"transgressive people whose behaviors we don't want to condone"},{"time":964000,"text":"to being AIDS victims,"},{"time":966000,"text":"we come over all compassionate"},{"time":968000,"text":"and buy them incredibly expensive drugs for the rest of their lives."},{"time":970000,"text":"It doesn't make any sense"},{"time":972000,"text":"from a public health point of view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974000,"text":"I want to give what's very nearly the last word to Ines."},{"time":978000,"text":"Ines is a a transgender hooker on the streets of Jakarta;"},{"time":981000,"text":"she's a chick with a dick."},{"time":983000,"text":"Why does she do that job?"},{"time":985000,"text":"Well, of course, because she's forced into it"},{"time":988000,"text":"because she doesn't have any better option, etc., etc."},{"time":990000,"text":"And if we could just teach her to sew"},{"time":992000,"text":"and get her a nice job in a factory, all would be well."},{"time":995000,"text":"This is what factory workers earn in an hour in Indonesia:"},{"time":997000,"text":"on average, 20 cents."},{"time":999000,"text":"It varies a bit province to province."},{"time":1001000,"text":"I do speak to sex workers, 15,000 of them"},{"time":1004000,"text":"for this particular slide,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and this is what sex workers"},{"time":1008000,"text":"say they earn in an hour."},{"time":1010000,"text":"So it's not a great job, but for a lot of people"},{"time":1013000,"text":"it really is quite a rational choice."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Okay, Ines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020000,"text":"We've got the tools, the knowledge and the cash,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"and commitment to preventing HIV too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"Ines: So why is prevalence still rising?"},{"time":1035000,"text":"It's all politics."},{"time":1038000,"text":"When you get to politics, nothing makes sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"Elizabeth Pisani: \"When you get to politics, nothing makes sense.\""},{"time":1044000,"text":"So, from the point of view of a sex worker,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"politicians are making no sense."},{"time":1049000,"text":"From the point of view of a public health nerd,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"junkies are doing dumb things."},{"time":1055000,"text":"The truth is that everyone has a different rationale."},{"time":1058000,"text":"There are as many different ways of being rational"},{"time":1060000,"text":"as there are human beings on the planet,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"and that's one of the glories of human existence."},{"time":1064000,"text":"But those ways of being rational"},{"time":1066000,"text":"are not independent of one another,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"so it's rational for"},{"time":1070000,"text":"a drug injector to share needles"},{"time":1072000,"text":"because of a stupid decision that's made by a politician,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"and it's rational for a politician"},{"time":1077000,"text":"to make that stupid decision"},{"time":1080000,"text":"because they're responding to"},{"time":1082000,"text":"what they think the voters want."},{"time":1084000,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":1086000,"text":"we are the voters."},{"time":1088000,"text":"We're not all of them, of course, but TED is a community of opinion leaders."},{"time":1091000,"text":"And everyone who's in this room,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and everyone who's watching this out there on the web,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"I think, has a duty to demand of their politicians"},{"time":1099000,"text":"that we make policy based on scientific evidence"},{"time":1102000,"text":"and on common sense."},{"time":1104000,"text":"It's going to be really hard for us"},{"time":1106000,"text":"to individually affect what's rational"},{"time":1109000,"text":"for every Frankie and every Ines out there,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"but you can at least use your vote"},{"time":1114000,"text":"to stop politicians doing stupid things"},{"time":1117000,"text":"that spread HIV."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1119000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}